  "expected": "number",
  "code": "invalid_type",
  "received": "NaN",
  "path": ["port"],
  "message": "Invalid input: expected number, received NaN"
}
```

The `received: "NaN"` key IS present here, even though the general rule in Zod v4 is that `received` is absent from `invalid_type` issues. The NaN case appears to be a special-cased exception. Other type mismatches (e.g., passing a number where a string is expected) do not include `received`.

