## Root cause (from hands-on evidence)

# Surprises — L8 Capstone Web Chat

## Eve 0.11.x requires Next.js 16, not 15

`npm install next@^15` fails with a peer dependency conflict — `eve@0.11.2` declares `peerOptional next@"^16.0.0"`. Using `next@^16.0.0` (resolved to 16.2.9) is required.

## Session start returns 202, not 200

The Eve HTTP session API returns HTTP 202 Accepted (async workflow kick-off) for `POST /eve/v1/session`, not 200. Assertion scripts must accept both 200 and 202 or use `status >= 200 && status < 300`.

## `await streamRes.text()` hangs on NDJSON streams

The NDJSON stream does not send a final `Content-Length` header and does not immediately close after the last event. `await streamRes.text()` blocks until the server closes the TCP connection, which can be much longer than the actual agent turn. Fix: read the stream chunk by chunk with `reader.read()` and break on `message.completed`.

## `withEve` is NOT invoked by `VERCEL=1 eve build` alone

The proven prebuilt recipe (`VERCEL=1 eve build` → `vercel deploy --prebuilt`) deploys ONLY the Eve HTTP service. It does NOT build or include the Next.js web pages. To deploy both:
- Do NOT use `--prebuilt`
- Use `vercel deploy --prod` (no `--prebuilt`) with `vercel.json` pointing to `next build` as the build command
- `withEve` inside `next.config.ts` intercepts the Next.js build, runs `eve build` internally, and merges the Eve output into the Next.js Vercel output bundle

## `withEve` adds a service prefix to Eve routes

In production (on Vercel), `withEve` mounts the Eve service at `/_eve_internal/eve` and rewrites `/eve/v1/*` to that internal prefix. The browser always talks to `/eve/v1/*` (same origin) and Next.js rewrites transparently. This means `useEveAgent` in a Next.js app needs no `host` config — it auto-discovers the Eve routes.

## tsconfig.json jsx conflict warning during build

`npx eve build` logs a `CONFIGURATION_FIELD_CONFLICT` warning about `compilerOptions.jsx` being overridden by the transform. This is harmless and does not affect the build output. Eve's internal transform takes priority over the tsconfig `jsx` setting.

## Vercel SSO protection gates even the public health route

As noted in L0: Vercel SSO is enabled by default and intercepts all routes (including `GET /eve/v1/health`) with an HTML login page before Eve can handle them. Must disable via `PATCH /v9/projects/{id} {"ssoProtection":null}` for any public-facing smoke.


